										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<h1 class="has-text-align-center"><strong>9 Discount Strategies You Can Use Today (Without Hurting Sales)</strong></h1>
<div class="post-content-category"><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/category/conversion-rate-optimization" rel="category tag">Conversion Rate Optimization</a></div>


<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-large"><img width="1024" height="437" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-1024x437.jpg" alt="Discount Strategy (WordPress)" class="wp-image-75377" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-1024x437.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-300x128.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-768x328.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-1536x656.jpg 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-380x162.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-600x256.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-760x325.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-1440x615.jpg 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-960x410.jpg 960w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-82x35.jpg 82w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-117x50.jpg 117w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-740x316.jpg 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-220x94.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress-385x164.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Discount-Strategy-Wordpress.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>


<div id="preamble-block_5e74a2c72323e" class="block-preamble"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Discounting has long been used to incentivize customers and prospects to make a purchase.</span></p>
</div>






<p>It’s not a new strategy, but it is an effective one—when marketers follow a few best practices.<br></p>



<p>The problem, though, is oftentimes marketers will offer sitewide discounts to their entire audience—without considering where visitors are in the buyer’s journey.<br></p>



<p>Sure, that might drum up more sales, but it can hurt your bottom line in the long run.<br></p>



<p>The solution, then, is to strike a balance between when and how often to use them and which user segment to offer them to.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>In this article, I’ll show you 9 different ways you can use discounts to get more sales. Plus, I’ll include alternatives for each tactic if discounting isn&#8217;t a viable option.&nbsp;<br></p>


<div id="contentupgrade-block_5e6b6231abd15" class="block-content-upgrade">
