<p><a href="#4">4. Make Your Call-To-Action Button the Center of Attention to Drive More Clicks</a></p>



<p><a href="#5">5. Use Fewer Input Fields to Increase Conversion Rates</a></p>



<p><a href="#6">6. Choose the Right Type of Form for Your Message</a></p>



<p><a href="#7">7. Customize Design for Different Devices to Avoid Annoying Google</a></p>



<p><a href="#8">8. Use Color Contrast to Highlight Text and Actions</a></p>



<p><a href="#9">9. Get Your Spacing Right (Without a Graphic Designer)</a></p>



<p><a href="#10">10. Create New Shape Illusions with .png Images</a></p>



<p><a href="#11">11. How to Choose the Right Fonts for Your Popup</a></p>



<h2 id="1"><strong>1. Match the Design of Your Popup with the Design of Your Site</strong></h2>



<p>No matter what type of popup you create, it needs to compliment your website.<br></p>



<p>At the same time, though, paradoxically, it needs to distinguish itself from your website’s content. (If it’s going to capture your visitors’ attention, that is.)<br></p>



<p>One way to match your popup design with your site is by using a color palette like <a href="https://color.adobe.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Adobe Color</a>.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>Upload a screengrab of your website—or the page you will show the popup on—and Adobe Color will tell you which colors appear in the screenshot.<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="868" height="452" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Adobe-Color-Color-Identifier.gif" alt="Adobe Color Color Identifier" class="wp-image-86867"/></figure></div>



<p>A great example of a brand using their website’s design in its popup is <a href="https://www.platinumtradingacademy.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Platinum Trading Academy</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="552" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Platinum-Trading-Academy-1024x552.jpg" alt="Platinum Trading Academy" class="wp-image-86927" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Platinum-Trading-Academy-1024x552.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Platinum-Trading-Academy-300x162.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Platinum-Trading-Academy-768x414.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Platinum-Trading-Academy-380x205.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Platinum-Trading-Academy-600x324.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Platinum-Trading-Academy-760x410.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Platinum-Trading-Academy-65x35.jpg 65w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Platinum-Trading-Academy-93x50.jpg 93w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Platinum-Trading-Academy-740x399.jpg 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Platinum-Trading-Academy-220x119.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Platinum-Trading-Academy-385x208.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Platinum-Trading-Academy.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Their popup matches the colors on the page without disappearing into the background. Moreover, the dark blue color differentiates itself from the light gray colors on the site, making it stand out further.<br></p>



<p>When creating popups based on your site’s color scheme, they will come across as less intrusive–making your visitors more likely to click through and convert.<br></p>



<p>(If you want more information on how to choose the right colors for your popups, <a href="https://sleeknote.com/academy/how-to-choose-the-right-color-palette" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">check out our Sleeknote Academy lesson</a>.)<br></p>





<h2 id="2"><strong>2. Experiment with New Shapes to Capture Attention</strong></h2>



<p>Did you know a popup’s content doesn’t have to stay inside the box?<br></p>



<p>You can experiment with different shapes in your popups to make them more unique and eye-catching. In fact, the more distinctive a popup is, the more likely it will stand out.<br></p>



<p>Fortunately, they’re just as easy to create as square popups. You simply create images in different shapes and then add them as floating images to your popup.<br></p>



<p>Here’s a unique example from <a href="https://woodupp.dk/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">WoodUpp</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="652" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Woodup-SleekBox-Example-1024x652.jpg" alt="Woodup SleekBox Example" class="wp-image-86963" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Woodup-SleekBox-Example-1024x652.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Woodup-SleekBox-Example-300x191.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Woodup-SleekBox-Example-768x489.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Woodup-SleekBox-Example-380x242.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Woodup-SleekBox-Example-600x382.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Woodup-SleekBox-Example-760x484.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Woodup-SleekBox-Example-55x35.jpg 55w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Woodup-SleekBox-Example-79x50.jpg 79w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Woodup-SleekBox-Example-740x471.jpg 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Woodup-SleekBox-Example-220x140.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Woodup-SleekBox-Example-385x245.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Woodup-SleekBox-Example.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>By having the images in uncommon shapes around the edges of the popup, WoodUpp shows more product images without hiding the popup’s copy.<br></p>



<p>Pretty clever, huh?<br></p>



<p>To learn more about how to create images in different shapes using Photoshop, <a href="https://www.photoshopessentials.com/photo-effects/place-image-inside-shape-photoshop/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">read this in-depth guide</a>.<br></p>





<h2 id="3"><strong>3. Use Color Blocks on Background Images to Increase Readability</strong></h2>



<p>I’m a big fan of background images in popups.<br></p>



<p>And for good reason:<br></p>



<p><em>They ensure your popups are more noticeable and showcase your products better.</em><br></p>



<p>When you use a background image in your popup, it’s sometimes hard to read the copy because it often clashes with the image’s colors.<br></p>



<p>Fortunately, there’s a fix for that.<br></p>



<p><em>Use see-through color blocks to highlight your copy.</em><br></p>



<p>Let me show you an example.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>Danish furniture store, <a href="https://mobelhuset2.dk/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Møbelhuset 2</a>, use white see-through blocks behind their copy:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="766" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Example-1024x766.jpg" alt="Møbelhuset SleekBox Example" class="wp-image-86911" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Example-1024x766.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Example-300x225.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Example-768x575.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Example-380x284.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Example-600x449.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Example-760x569.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Example-47x35.jpg 47w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Example-67x50.jpg 67w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Example-655x490.jpg 655w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Example-220x165.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Example-385x288.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Example.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Now, watch what happens when I remove the color blocks:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="766" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Without-Text-Block-1024x766.jpg" alt="Møbelhuset SleekBox Without Text Block" class="wp-image-86915" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Without-Text-Block-1024x766.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Without-Text-Block-300x225.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Without-Text-Block-768x575.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Without-Text-Block-380x284.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Without-Text-Block-600x449.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Without-Text-Block-760x569.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Without-Text-Block-47x35.jpg 47w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Without-Text-Block-67x50.jpg 67w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Without-Text-Block-655x490.jpg 655w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Without-Text-Block-220x165.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Without-Text-Block-385x288.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Møbelhuset-SleekBox-Without-Text-Block.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Big difference, right?<br></p>



<p>The color blocks make the copy much easier to read—and without blocking the background images.<br></p>



<p>To create a color block, create a new image in Photoshop using the dimensions you want. Then, change the opacity of the color. (In the above example, the opacity is set to 80%.)<br></p>



<p>You can add blocks in different colors depending on the colors found in the background image:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="701" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Salad-Recipes-SleekBox-Example-1024x701.jpg" alt="Salad Recipes SleekBox Example" class="wp-image-86943" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Salad-Recipes-SleekBox-Example-1024x701.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Salad-Recipes-SleekBox-Example-300x206.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Salad-Recipes-SleekBox-Example-768x526.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Salad-Recipes-SleekBox-Example-380x260.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Salad-Recipes-SleekBox-Example-600x411.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Salad-Recipes-SleekBox-Example-760x521.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Salad-Recipes-SleekBox-Example-51x35.jpg 51w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Salad-Recipes-SleekBox-Example-73x50.jpg 73w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Salad-Recipes-SleekBox-Example-715x490.jpg 715w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Salad-Recipes-SleekBox-Example-220x151.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Salad-Recipes-SleekBox-Example-385x264.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Salad-Recipes-SleekBox-Example.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>





<h2 id="4"><strong>4. Make Your Call-To-Action Button the Center of Attention to Drive More Clicks</strong></h2>



<p>Your visitors should NEVER feel confused about what to do or where to click when they see a popup.<br></p>



<p>So, with that in mind, you need to ensure that your <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/call-to-action" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">call-to-action</a> (CTA) is a key part of your popup and uses <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/persuasive-copywriting-techniques" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">benefit-driven copy</a> to encourage visitors to click through.<br></p>



<p>Take this example from <a href="https://www.evasolo.com/en/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Eva Solo</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="508" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Example-1024x508.jpg" alt="Eva Solo SleekBox Example" class="wp-image-86895" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Example-1024x508.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Example-300x149.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Example-768x381.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Example-380x188.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Example-600x298.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Example-760x377.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Example-71x35.jpg 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Example-101x50.jpg 101w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Example-740x367.jpg 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Example-220x109.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Example-385x191.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Example.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>The CTA button focuses on the value of the offer: “Enter to Win [the competition] Now,” and the black color against the white background ensures that the user won’t overlook it.<br></p>



<p>The same applies if you use two CTA buttons:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="612" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-with-Two-CTA-Buttons-1024x612.jpg" alt="SleekBox with Two CTA Buttons" class="wp-image-86955" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-with-Two-CTA-Buttons-1024x612.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-with-Two-CTA-Buttons-300x179.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-with-Two-CTA-Buttons-768x459.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-with-Two-CTA-Buttons-380x227.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-with-Two-CTA-Buttons-600x359.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-with-Two-CTA-Buttons-760x454.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-with-Two-CTA-Buttons-59x35.jpg 59w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-with-Two-CTA-Buttons-84x50.jpg 84w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-with-Two-CTA-Buttons-740x442.jpg 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-with-Two-CTA-Buttons-220x131.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-with-Two-CTA-Buttons-385x230.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-with-Two-CTA-Buttons.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Many e-commerce sites use two CTA buttons to force visitors to make a choice. But many use negative language in their second button copy to get more people to sign up, such as “no, I don’t like discounts” or “No, I want to pay full price.”<br></p>



<p>Just because visitors don’t click through in your popups, doesn’t mean they won’t turn into customers.<br></p>



<p>So refrain from using negative language in your CTA buttons, and give them the option to continue browsing your site instead of annoying them.<br></p>





<h2 id="5"><strong>5. Use Fewer Input Fields to Increase Conversion Rates</strong></h2>



<p>Let me ask you a question:<br></p>



<p>Can you remove an input field from one of your popups and still get in touch with those who sign up?<br></p>



<p>If the answer is yes, you probably have too many input fields.<br></p>



<p>I know it’s always nice to have as much information about your prospects as possible, but our data tells us that every time you add an input field you can expect your conversion rate to decrease by 50 percent.<br></p>



<p>Keep in mind that if you only ask for an email address, you can always <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/follow-up-emails" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">follow up via email</a> and ask for more information.<br></p>



<p>Let me show you an example.<br></p>



<p>Here’s a campaign with two input fields:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Two-Input-Fields.jpg" alt="A SleekBox with Two Input Fields" class="wp-image-86863" width="450" height="707" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Two-Input-Fields.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Two-Input-Fields-191x300.jpg 191w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Two-Input-Fields-380x597.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Two-Input-Fields-22x35.jpg 22w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Two-Input-Fields-32x50.jpg 32w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Two-Input-Fields-312x490.jpg 312w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Two-Input-Fields-220x345.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Two-Input-Fields-385x604.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /></figure></div>



<p>Here’s the same campaign, but with four input fields and radio buttons:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="528" height="1024" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Multiple-Input-Fields-528x1024.jpg" alt="A SleekBox with Multiple Input Fields" class="wp-image-86859" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Multiple-Input-Fields-528x1024.jpg 528w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Multiple-Input-Fields-155x300.jpg 155w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Multiple-Input-Fields-380x737.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Multiple-Input-Fields-18x35.jpg 18w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Multiple-Input-Fields-26x50.jpg 26w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Multiple-Input-Fields-253x490.jpg 253w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Multiple-Input-Fields-220x427.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Multiple-Input-Fields-385x747.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/A-SleekBox-with-Multiple-Input-Fields.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 528px) 100vw, 528px" /></figure></div>



<p>Which one would you most likely want to fill out?<br></p>



<p>The one with fewer input fields, right?<br></p>



<p>Consumers are less willing to part with personal information, so keeping your input fields to a minimum will not just make your campaign look better, it’ll also increase your conversion rates.<br></p>





<h2 id="6"><strong>6. Choose the Right Type of Form for Your Message</strong></h2>



<p>Your popup’s design isn’t just about colors—it’s also about deciding what <em>type</em> of popup to use.<br></p>



<p>With Sleeknote, we offer three different types of popup to choose from:<br></p>



<ol><li>The popup</li><li>The slide-in</li><li>The bar</li></ol>



<p>Let’s go through each briefly.<br></p>





<h3><strong>i. The Popup</strong></h3>



<p>This is the form that pops up in the middle of the screen on top of the page content.&nbsp;<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="930" height="606" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Exit-Intent-SleekBox-Example.gif" alt="Exit-Intent SleekBox Example" class="wp-image-86903"/></figure></div>



<p>It’s the most “aggressive” type of popup and we recommend using it the <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/exit-intent" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">exit-intent</a> trigger or when visitors trigger a form with the click of a button. That way, you don’t interrupt visitors while they’re browsing your site.<br></p>



<p>When you use an exit-intent popup, you should make your form as attention-grabbing as possible. It’s your last chance to catch your visitors before they leave, so avoid creating a popup that blends in. It needs to stand out.<br></p>





<h3><strong>ii. The Slide-In</strong></h3>



<p>This is one of the most used types of popups because it subtly slides in from the bottom of the screen without blocking your site content.&nbsp;</p>







<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="320" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Eva-Solo-SleekBox-Slide-In.gif" alt="Eva Solo SleekBox Slide-In" class="wp-image-86899"/></figure></div>



<p>That means visitors can continue to browse your site without having to close the slide-in.<br></p>



<p>The most important takeaway to remember when designing a slide-in is to match it with the design of your site. (See strategy #1 for more on this).<br></p>



<p>With a slide-in and popup, you also have the option to include a teaser.<br></p>



<p>The teaser isn’t an actual form on its own, but rather an addition to your popup and slide-in forms.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>The teaser is a small bar that sits at the bottom of your screen when your form hasn’t been triggered or closed.&nbsp;<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="581" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-Teaser-Example-1024x581.jpg" alt="SleekBox Teaser Example" class="wp-image-86951" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-Teaser-Example-1024x581.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-Teaser-Example-300x170.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-Teaser-Example-768x436.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-Teaser-Example-380x216.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-Teaser-Example-600x341.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-Teaser-Example-760x431.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-Teaser-Example-62x35.jpg 62w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-Teaser-Example-88x50.jpg 88w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-Teaser-Example-740x420.jpg 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-Teaser-Example-220x125.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-Teaser-Example-385x218.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBox-Teaser-Example.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>It’s also the only thing your mobile visitors will see when you have a popup or a slide-in form on your mobile site.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>On mobile, your form will only trigger when a visitor clicks the teaser, ensuring a smooth mobile experience:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Mobile-Teaser.gif" alt="Mobile Teaser" class="wp-image-86923" width="450" height="746"/></figure></div>



<p>Your teaser should “tease” the content in your form (hence the name), and thus, shouldn’t include much content.<br></p>



<p>Create a compelling headline and a background color or background image, and that’s all you need.<br></p>





<h3><strong>iii. The Bar</strong></h3>



<p>The bar sits at the top or bottom of your screen.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="https://www.kingsqueens.dk/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Kings &amp; Queens</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="393" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBar-Sale-Example-1024x393.jpg" alt="SleekBar Sale Example" class="wp-image-86947" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBar-Sale-Example-1024x393.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBar-Sale-Example-300x115.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBar-Sale-Example-768x294.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBar-Sale-Example-380x146.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBar-Sale-Example-600x230.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBar-Sale-Example-760x291.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBar-Sale-Example-91x35.jpg 91w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBar-Sale-Example-130x50.jpg 130w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBar-Sale-Example-740x284.jpg 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBar-Sale-Example-220x84.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBar-Sale-Example-385x148.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/SleekBar-Sale-Example.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>This type of form is perfect for announcing an upcoming sale, promoting new product lines, or giving visitors an important message.<br></p>



<p>Because the bar doesn’t take up much screen space, you can be more bold with its colors.<br></p>



<p>So, if you’re teasing an upcoming sale, you can use a background color that contrasts the colors on your site.</p>


