										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<h1 class="has-text-align-center">How to Craft the Perfect Email Call-to-Action (+ Examples)</h1>
<div class="post-content-category"><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/category/email-marketing" rel="category tag">Email Marketing</a></div>


<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-large"><img width="1024" height="240" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-1024x240.jpg" alt="Email Call-to-Action [Wordpress]" class="wp-image-92583" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-1024x240.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-300x70.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-768x180.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-1536x360.jpg 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-2048x480.jpg 2048w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-380x89.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-600x141.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-760x178.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-1440x338.jpg 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-149x35.jpg 149w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-213x50.jpg 213w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-740x173.jpg 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-220x52.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Email-Call-to-Action-Wordpress-385x90.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>


<div id="preamble-block_5ea17dc75bc86" class="block-preamble"><p><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Learn More. Sign Up. Click Here. Shop Now</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;">. What do these phrases make you want to do? Nothing, right?</span></p>
</div>






<p>(Except maybe roll your eyes.)</p>



<p>They’re meant to drive readers to action, but because we see them so often, we filter them out when reading online content—especially when it comes to <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/e-commerce-email-marketing">email marketing</a>.</p>



<p>If you want your emails to stand out in your reader’s overcrowded inbox, you need to create email calls-to-action (CTAs) that compel readers to take action immediately—and that’s a difficult thing to do.</p>



<p>So today, I want to show you how to create email CTAs that your readers can’t help but click (with examples), so you can break through the noise and drive higher email engagement and sales.</p>



<p>But before I do&#8230;</p>


<div id="contentupgrade-block_5e6f42ca8dc98" class="block-content-upgrade">
    <div class="text">
        <p class="text-pretitle">FREE DOWNLOADABLE BONUS</p>
        <h2 class="text-title">Want More Email CTA Examples?</h2>
        <div class="text-content"><div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_4  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_dark">
<div class="et_pb_text_inner">
<p>Download our bonus resource to learn how to craft the perfect email call-to-action, step-by-step.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
                    <a onClick="SleekNote.triggerOnclick('00c91b9b-1dbc-48da-8d77-1dd2cfc8355b');" href="javascript:void(0);" class="text-link" title="Get My Bonus Resource →">Get My Bonus Resource →</a>
            </div>
    <div class="image">
        <img src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Grow-Your-Email-List@2x-1.png" title="Want More Email CTA Examples?">    </div>
</div>


<h2><strong>Why Are Email Calls-To-Action Different?</strong></h2>



<p>Before going into the details of <em>how</em> you create a compelling email CTA for your emails, you need to understand <em>why</em> they’re different.</p>



<p>The most obvious difference is that you have limited space to work with.</p>



<p>Every word in your email is part of your CTA, and there’s no room for getting sidetracked.</p>



<p>Every word in your email is in some way part of your CTA, which is the hard part about email CTAs.</p>



<p>You can start your email off by sharing a story about a recent experience you had at the grocery store, or blabber on about how furious you are with people in oversize t-shirts (or whatever makes you fly off the handle), as long as your story has a point and encourages readers to take action.</p>



<p>When you write a blog post or create a video, for instance, you have plenty of space to make use of different elements to help influence the reader to take action, such as visual cues (images, GIFs, body language, and so on).</p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="https://www.target.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Target</a>, where body language helps encourage viewers to take action:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="881" height="497" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image1-27.png" alt="Cooking Show" class="wp-image-92603" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image1-27.png 881w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image1-27-300x169.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image1-27-768x433.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image1-27-380x214.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image1-27-600x338.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image1-27-760x429.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image1-27-62x35.png 62w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image1-27-89x50.png 89w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image1-27-740x417.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image1-27-220x124.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image1-27-385x217.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 881px) 100vw, 881px" /></figure></div>



<p>Being limited by space isn’t necessarily a bad thing (and that’s coming from me “miss can’t-stop-writing”).</p>



<p>It forces you to consider every single word in your email, which will result in stronger copy and drive people to action.&nbsp;</p>



<p>With email CTAs, length doesn’t influence SERP rankings, and your reader’s attention is limited, so each word has to earn its way into your email with the purpose of maximizing the time you have with your readers.</p>



<p>Remember that a CTA is not just a simple button or a small sentence at the end of your email.</p>



<p>A good CTA starts with the subject line and follows all the way through the email to your PS.</p>



<p>Many marketers think of a CTA as a single element in their content that can drive people to action with one simple phrase:</p>



<p><em>Download. Join Now. Read More</em>.&nbsp;</p>



<p>It’s not.</p>



<p>Your button or link is only <em>part</em> of the CTA—admittedly an <em>important</em> part—but it doesn’t stand a chance on its own.&nbsp;</p>



<p>So how do you write an effective email CTA?</p>



<p>That’s what I’ll tell you now.</p>





<h2><strong>How to Create a Powerful Email Call-To-Action</strong></h2>



<p>There are a few elements to writing a powerful email CTA, and in this section, I’m going to break it down into three parts:</p>



<ol><li>Defining your goal</li><li>Writing the copy</li><li>Designing your CTA</li></ol>



<p>Let’s have a closer look at each one.</p>





<h3><strong>i. Define the Purpose of Your CTA</strong></h3>



<p>Before you start writing your CTA, you need to define the purpose of it.</p>



<p>What is the action you want people to take and how do you get them to take it?</p>



<p>Let’s say you run an e-commerce with clothing, and you want to email your list with the purpose of increasing sales on a new line of dresses.</p>



<p>Here’s what most businesses would do:</p>



<p>Create an email with images of the new dresses and finish off with a button that says: “Shop Now.”</p>



<p>Does it work?</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="292" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Shemar-Moore.gif" alt="Shemar Moore" class="wp-image-92595"/></figure></div>



<p>So here’s what you do instead.</p>



<p>You know <em>what</em> action you want people to take, so now you ask yourself <em>how</em>.</p>



<p>What value is your product giving people that they can’t get elsewhere?&nbsp;</p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="https://casper.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Casper</a>:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="722" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Casper-Email-CTA.jpg" alt="Casper Email CTA" class="wp-image-92563" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Casper-Email-CTA.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Casper-Email-CTA-249x300.jpg 249w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Casper-Email-CTA-380x457.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Casper-Email-CTA-29x35.jpg 29w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Casper-Email-CTA-42x50.jpg 42w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Casper-Email-CTA-407x490.jpg 407w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Casper-Email-CTA-220x265.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Casper-Email-CTA-385x463.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>Casper knows a concern of their <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/buyer-personas" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">buyer persona</a> is keeping bedsheets clean (nothing beats the feeling of new, clean bedsheets—am I right?)</p>



<p>They address this concern in the copy of their email and instead of writing “Shop Now” in their CTA button, they chose to write something that supports the CTA in the copy.</p>



<p>Now we’ve already touched upon it slightly, but let’s go into more detail on how to write the copy for your CTA.</p>





<h3><strong>ii. Write Compelling CTA Copy</strong></h3>



<p>Your CTA copy is what ultimately convinces your reader to take action—or not.</p>



<p>You must <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/e-commerce-value-proposition" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">create a killer value proposition</a> if you want people to click-through.</p>



<p>Dale Carnegie, author of the classic <a href="http://www.samuelthomasdavies.com/book-summaries/self-help/how-to-win-friends-and-influence-people/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><em>How to Win Friends &amp; Influence People</em></a>, puts it this way: “The only way on earth to influence other people is to talk about what they want and show them how to get it.”</p>



<p>Each of the CTAs in your email should trigger a different emotion in your reader.</p>



<p>For instance, <a href="https://www.chubbiesshorts.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Chubbies</a> taps into people’s <a href="https://neilpatel.com/blog/how-to-use-cialdinis-principles-of-persuasion-to-improve-your-content-marketing-strategy/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">fear of missing out</a> to get people to click their CTA button:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="832" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Chubbies-Email-CTA.jpg" alt="Chubbies Email CTA" class="wp-image-92567" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Chubbies-Email-CTA.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Chubbies-Email-CTA-216x300.jpg 216w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Chubbies-Email-CTA-380x527.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Chubbies-Email-CTA-25x35.jpg 25w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Chubbies-Email-CTA-36x50.jpg 36w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Chubbies-Email-CTA-353x490.jpg 353w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Chubbies-Email-CTA-220x305.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Chubbies-Email-CTA-385x534.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p><a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.curioos.com/" target="_blank">Curioos</a>, meanwhile, lures readers in with the promise of getting lost in a dream world, tapping into their curiosity:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="670" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Curioos-Email-CTA.jpg" alt="Curioos Email CTA" class="wp-image-92571" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Curioos-Email-CTA.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Curioos-Email-CTA-269x300.jpg 269w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Curioos-Email-CTA-380x424.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Curioos-Email-CTA-31x35.jpg 31w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Curioos-Email-CTA-45x50.jpg 45w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Curioos-Email-CTA-439x490.jpg 439w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Curioos-Email-CTA-220x246.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Curioos-Email-CTA-385x430.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>Don’t use the same CTA throughout your email. Switch it up and trigger different emotions with your CTAs.</p>



<p>The action is the same, but your approach is different.</p>



<p>Many marketers use the same CTA throughout their email and then reuse that CTA in the next email, and the next, and the next (I could go on, but I’ll spare you).</p>



<p>By adding multiple CTAs that have the same goal but conveyed differently, you increase chances of “hitting your readers’ sweet spots” and get them to click.</p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="https://www.trunkclub.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Trunk Club</a>:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="680" height="706" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image2-3.jpg" alt="Trunk Club" class="wp-image-92607" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image2-3.jpg 680w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image2-3-289x300.jpg 289w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image2-3-380x395.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image2-3-600x623.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image2-3-34x35.jpg 34w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image2-3-48x50.jpg 48w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image2-3-472x490.jpg 472w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image2-3-220x228.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image2-3-385x400.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure></div>



<p>In the first part of the email, they introduce their new feature along with a CTA.</p>



<p>The second part of the email gives a more thorough description of the feature along with a new call-to-action that has the same purpose as the first.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="680" height="897" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image6-3.jpg" alt="Trunk Scheduling Possibilities" class="wp-image-92611" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image6-3.jpg 680w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image6-3-227x300.jpg 227w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image6-3-380x501.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image6-3-600x791.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image6-3-27x35.jpg 27w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image6-3-38x50.jpg 38w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image6-3-371x490.jpg 371w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image6-3-220x290.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/image6-3-385x508.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure></div>



<p>In extension to this, I want to emphasize the importance of NOT writing “sign up” or “click here”.</p>



<p>Whether you’re using buttons or embedded text (more on that later), your CTA should never be generic.</p>



<p>People need to differentiate between the CTAs and know which one to click when they want to take a certain action.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="125" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Smashing-Magazine-CTA.jpg" alt="Smashing Magazine CTA" class="wp-image-92599" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Smashing-Magazine-CTA.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Smashing-Magazine-CTA-300x63.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Smashing-Magazine-CTA-380x79.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Smashing-Magazine-CTA-168x35.jpg 168w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Smashing-Magazine-CTA-240x50.jpg 240w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Smashing-Magazine-CTA-220x46.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Smashing-Magazine-CTA-385x80.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2012/06/links-should-never-say-click-here/" target="_blank">Smashing Magazine</a></em></p>





<p>See the difference?</p>



<p>By just writing “click here”, you’re concealing what the user is actually clicking.&nbsp;</p>



<p>When writing your CTA, keep it <strong>short, relevant, and intriguing</strong>.</p>





<h3>i<strong>ii. How to Design a Call-To-Action Readers Will Click</strong></h3>



<p>Once your CTA copy is on point, there are a few final things you should consider before sending your email.</p>



<p>First, you should never include too many CTAs in your email.</p>



<p>This doesn’t mean you can’t include multiple links and buttons; <em>it just means the purpose of them must be the same in each</em>.</p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="https://greenchef.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Green Chef</a>:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="421" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-1.jpg" alt="Green Chef Email CTA 1" class="wp-image-92587" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-1.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-1-300x211.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-1-380x267.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-1-50x35.jpg 50w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-1-71x50.jpg 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-1-220x154.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-1-385x270.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>They start out by addressing a <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/psychology-based-pricing-strategies" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">common pricing problem</a>: buying organic can be expensive.</p>



<p>Green Chef knows people don’t always read the entire email so they’ve added a call-to-action where people can try their product for free (again addresses the concern over price).</p>



<p>This is the second part of the email:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="377" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-2.jpg" alt="Green Chef Email CTA 2" class="wp-image-92591" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-2.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-2-300x189.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-2-380x239.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-2-56x35.jpg 56w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-2-80x50.jpg 80w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-2-220x138.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Green-Chef-Email-CTA-2-385x242.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>They then overcome the price objection and convince the reader their product is more affordable than in regular grocery stores.</p>



<p>Green Chef still addresses the same concern, and even though the button here is different, it still has the same purpose: Get people to try Green Chef.</p>



<p>If you use buttons, be careful not to add too many.</p>



<p>Doing so will create confusion, and readers will refrain from clicking them.</p>



<p>Another option is to use <strong>embedded commands</strong> in the copy.</p>



<p>Few marketers are doing this, and the only way to see if it works for you is to test it.</p>



<p>Embedded commands are in-text links, meaning you link a part of a sentence instead of adding buttons.&nbsp;</p>



<p>By adding embedded commands in the copy, you avoid breaking up the flow of the email, and it becomes more readable.</p>



<p>You also appeal to skim readers (and trust me, they’re many). A skim reader is much more likely to click a link that has a command such as “Try the new fragrance now” than a simple “click here”.</p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="https://www.beardbrand.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Beardbrand</a>:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="598" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Email-CTA.jpg" alt="Beardbrand Email CTA" class="wp-image-92559" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Email-CTA.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Email-CTA-300x300.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Email-CTA-150x150.jpg 150w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Email-CTA-380x379.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Email-CTA-35x35.jpg 35w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Email-CTA-50x50.jpg 50w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Email-CTA-492x490.jpg 492w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Email-CTA-220x219.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Email-CTA-385x384.jpg 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Beardbrand-Email-CTA-120x120.jpg 120w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>There are no buttons to click, but the message is still clear: “try the Sea Salt Spray.”</p>



<p>A good rule of thumb is that if you have a lot of text in your emails, you should use embedded commands, and if you have a lot of visuals (product images, and so on) buttons tend to be more effective.</p>



<p>But, like I always say, you should test it to see which option works best for your emails.</p>


