<h2>Table of Contents</h2>



<p><a href="#1">1. Manual Follow-Up Emails</a></p>



<p><a href="#2">2. Trigger-Based Follow-Up Emails</a></p>



<p><a href="#3">3. Time-Based Follow-Up Emails</a></p>



<h2 id="1"><strong>1. Manual Follow-Up Emails</strong></h2>



<p>Now, I know marketers are not fans of the word manual, but sometimes a little manual labor is necessary.<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="256" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Ryan-Reynolds-Manual-Labor.gif" alt="Ryan Reynolds Manual Labor" class="wp-image-73975"/></figure></div>



<p>We focus so much on automating everything that we sometimes forget the power of a handwritten message, or in this case—a handwritten email.<br></p>



<p>Manual follow-up emails are not that time-consuming and they can have a great effect on your conversion rate and customer satisfaction.<br></p>



<p>You can even create message templates for your manual emails to increase efficiency (I’ll explain later so keep reading).<br></p>



<p>So, what types of personal handwritten emails should you send?<br></p>



<p>It depends on the individual prospect you’ve been in touch with and what your conversation was about.<br></p>



<p>Let’s take a look at a few examples.</p>



<h3><strong>i. The “Need More Options” Email</strong></h3>



<p>If a prospect is in doubt and not sure what exactly they’re looking for, providing additional product recommendations can be effective.<br></p>



<p>Let me show you how it can be done.<br></p>



<p>I recently engaged in a live chat on <a href="http://us.asos.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">ASOS</a> because I needed to find a pair of shoes for my cousin’s wedding.<br></p>



<p>I gave the customer service agent a description of what I was looking for and sent her a picture of the dress I was wearing. She then gave me a few options matching my requirements.<br></p>



<p>I wasn’t completely sold on her suggestions so I said I needed some time to think about it.<br></p>



<p>I then received this email from her moments later:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="452" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/ASOS-Live-Chat-Follow-Up-Email.jpg" alt="ASOS Live Chat Follow-Up Email" class="wp-image-73915" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/ASOS-Live-Chat-Follow-Up-Email.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/ASOS-Live-Chat-Follow-Up-Email-300x226.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/ASOS-Live-Chat-Follow-Up-Email-380x286.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/ASOS-Live-Chat-Follow-Up-Email-46x35.jpg 46w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/ASOS-Live-Chat-Follow-Up-Email-66x50.jpg 66w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/ASOS-Live-Chat-Follow-Up-Email-220x166.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/ASOS-Live-Chat-Follow-Up-Email-385x290.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>Amazing right?<br></p>



<p>She offers further suggestions, and even compliments my choice of clothes.<br></p>



<p>Needless to say, I ended up buying TWO pairs of shoes because I was astonished by the level of customer service I received (my shopaholic tendencies shouldn’t come as a surprise anymore).<br></p>



<p>Look at your follow-up emails as an extension of the conversation you just had, and build on what you talked about to make the sale.<br></p>



<h3><strong>ii. The “Need More Information” Email</strong></h3>



<p>Sometimes prospects need a little more information before making a purchase decision.<br></p>



<p>This is particularly relevant with more expensive and complex products such as electronics, furniture, and so on.<br></p>



<p>You might not have all the information about a product available during a call or live chat, so you can offer to send the information by email.<br></p>



<p>That way you get an email address (read: a new lead for your campaigns), and the prospect has the information handy at all times.<br></p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="https://bonobos.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Bonobos</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="257" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Bonobos-Follow-Up-Email.jpg" alt="Bonobos Follow-Up Email" class="wp-image-73931" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Bonobos-Follow-Up-Email.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Bonobos-Follow-Up-Email-300x129.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Bonobos-Follow-Up-Email-380x163.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Bonobos-Follow-Up-Email-82x35.jpg 82w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Bonobos-Follow-Up-Email-117x50.jpg 117w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Bonobos-Follow-Up-Email-220x94.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Bonobos-Follow-Up-Email-385x165.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>During a recent live chat with them, we talked about how to find the right size (I was looking for a new suit for my better half, and wasn’t sure of the size), and I wanted to have the information handy for when I got a chance to take measures and find the right size.<br></p>



<p>You should also offer your prospects to send them a transcript of your live chat, in case they need the information you provided for later.<br></p>



<p>With this type of follow-up email, you can create a template to save you time.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>For instance:<br></p>



<p><em>Hi [NAME],</em><br></p>



<p><em>Here’s the information you requested:</em><br></p>



<p><em>[INFORMATION GOES HERE]</em><br></p>



<p><em>Hope this helps, and please let me know if there’s anything else I can help you with.</em><br></p>



<p><em>Have a great day!”</em><br></p>



<p>If you send additional information to help a prospect make a decision, don’t forget to follow up to make sure they make a decision and buy.<br></p>



<h3><strong>iii. The “Deal Closing” Email</strong></h3>



<p>As the name implies, this email is the one you send when a prospect is at the bottom of your sales funnel, and ready to buy.<br></p>



<p>Let’s say you run a travel agency and you’ve just had a call with a prospect regarding an offer on a skiing trip to the alps.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>You want to send the offer to the prospect right away so they can review and confirm.<br></p>



<p>One of the most effective ways to do that is to offer a custom quote using a page-specific popup. Watch the video below to learn how to do that using Sleeknote:<br></p>



<div style="height:40px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<script src="https://fast.wistia.com/embed/medias/25got9ptpz.jsonp" async=""></script><script src="https://fast.wistia.com/assets/external/E-v1.js" async=""></script><div class="wistia_responsive_padding" style="padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;"><div class="wistia_responsive_wrapper" style="height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%;"><div class="wistia_embed wistia_async_25got9ptpz videoFoam=true" style="height:100%;position:relative;width:100%"><div class="wistia_swatch" style="height:100%;left:0;opacity:0;overflow:hidden;position:absolute;top:0;transition:opacity 200ms;width:100%;"><img src="https://fast.wistia.com/embed/medias/25got9ptpz/swatch" style="filter:blur(5px);height:100%;object-fit:contain;width:100%;" alt="" aria-hidden="true" onload="this.parentNode.style.opacity=1;"></div></div></div></div>



<h3><strong>iv. The “Don’t Go Just Yet” Email&nbsp;</strong></h3>



<p>One important rule in marketing is to not give up.<br></p>



<p>In the words of <a href="http://www.chumba.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Chumbawamba</a>: “I get knocked down, but I get up again.”<br></p>



<p>(I really love that tune!)<br></p>



<p>Just because you didn’t make a sale during live chat or your call, doesn’t mean your chance is lost.<br></p>



<p>There are many reasons people don’t buy during the first contact (in fact, very few do), so try to figure out what that reason is and address that in your email.<br></p>



<p>Maybe they didn’t have time, or the price wasn’t right.<br></p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="https://www.madsencycles.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Madsen Cycles</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="288" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Madsen-Cycles-Follow-Up-Email.jpg" alt="Madsen Cycles Follow-Up Email" class="wp-image-73959" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Madsen-Cycles-Follow-Up-Email.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Madsen-Cycles-Follow-Up-Email-300x144.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Madsen-Cycles-Follow-Up-Email-380x182.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Madsen-Cycles-Follow-Up-Email-73x35.jpg 73w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Madsen-Cycles-Follow-Up-Email-104x50.jpg 104w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Madsen-Cycles-Follow-Up-Email-220x106.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Madsen-Cycles-Follow-Up-Email-385x185.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>Instead of asking visitors to buy, they ask what prevented them from buying.<br></p>



<p>That way they can start a dialogue with prospects and perhaps make the sale after all by eliminating the concerns that prevented them from buying in the first place.<br></p>



<p>If you’ve had a call with them, they will have already given you an indication of why they’re not ready to buy yet.<br></p>



<p>Most of the above email can be templatized so you only need to make a small adjustment before sending.<br></p>



<h2 id="2"><strong>2. Trigger-Based Follow-Up Emails</strong></h2>



<p>Now that you’ve got the hang of manual emails, we can move on to what you love &#8230;&nbsp;<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Mr.-Bean.jpg" alt="Mr. Bean" class="wp-image-73967" width="450" height="424" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Mr.-Bean.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Mr.-Bean-300x283.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Mr.-Bean-380x358.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Mr.-Bean-37x35.jpg 37w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Mr.-Bean-53x50.jpg 53w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Mr.-Bean-520x490.jpg 520w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Mr.-Bean-220x207.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Mr.-Bean-385x363.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /></figure></div>



<p>Trigger-based emails are sent whenever a user has triggered a certain action, such as abandoning their cart, clicked a certain link, or any other type of trigger.<br></p>



<p>So what type of triggers should you follow up on?<br></p>



<p>Let’s see…<br></p>



<h3><strong>i. The “What Did We Do Wrong?” Email</strong></h3>



<p>You always want to collect feedback from your prospects, to gather useful insights on how to improve.<br></p>



<p>If you’re not sending manual messages to prospects after they’ve been in contact with you, you should at the very least ask for their feedback.<br></p>



<p>It’s not so much about what you did wrong, but more about how you can improve.<br></p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="http://shop.nordstrom.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Nordstrom</a> who I recently had a live chat conversation with:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="505" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Nordstrom-Feedback-Email.jpg" alt="Nordstrom Feedback Email" class="wp-image-73971" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Nordstrom-Feedback-Email.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Nordstrom-Feedback-Email-300x253.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Nordstrom-Feedback-Email-380x320.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Nordstrom-Feedback-Email-42x35.jpg 42w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Nordstrom-Feedback-Email-59x50.jpg 59w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Nordstrom-Feedback-Email-582x490.jpg 582w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Nordstrom-Feedback-Email-220x185.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Nordstrom-Feedback-Email-385x324.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>While Nordstrom has kept the email simple, they could easily have made it more personal with a few merge tags, like <a href="https://mailchimp.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">MailChimp</a> does in their email:</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="476" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MailChimp-Support-Feedback-Email.jpg" alt="MailChimp Support Feedback Email" class="wp-image-73963" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MailChimp-Support-Feedback-Email.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MailChimp-Support-Feedback-Email-300x238.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MailChimp-Support-Feedback-Email-380x301.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MailChimp-Support-Feedback-Email-44x35.jpg 44w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MailChimp-Support-Feedback-Email-63x50.jpg 63w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MailChimp-Support-Feedback-Email-220x175.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MailChimp-Support-Feedback-Email-385x305.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>







<p>They use my name and at the bottom and they remind me what my ticket was about in case I forgot (I’m quite forgetful so I appreciate small details like that).<br></p>



<p>(I cut out the long correspondence so I wouldn’t bore you with the details of it)<br></p>



<p>This email was sent after I had been in touch with their support team. You always want to get feedback on your customer support—both the good and the bad.<br></p>



<p>Don’t create long surveys even though it might seem like a good idea to get TONS of information—because it’s not. No one has time to answer a 30-minute survey, so make it easy for people to give their feedback.<br></p>



<h3><strong>ii. The “Did You Forgot Something?” Email</strong></h3>



<p>We can’t do a post on follow-up emails and not include <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/abandoned-cart-emails" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">abandoned cart emails</a>.<br></p>



<p>According to Shopify, <a href="https://www.shopify.com/blog/12522201-13-amazing-abandoned-cart-emails-and-what-you-can-learn-from-them" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">67.45% people put items in their online shopping cart only to leave it</a> without completing their purchase.<br></p>



<p>That’s why it’s important to follow-up on abandoned carts and encourage people to return to their cart and complete their purchase.<br></p>



<p>Here’s how <a href="https://www.hermanmiller.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Herman Miller</a> does that:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="400" height="567" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Herman-Miller-Abandoned-Cart-Email.jpg" alt="Herman Miller Abandoned Cart Email" class="wp-image-73955" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Herman-Miller-Abandoned-Cart-Email.jpg 400w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Herman-Miller-Abandoned-Cart-Email-212x300.jpg 212w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Herman-Miller-Abandoned-Cart-Email-380x539.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Herman-Miller-Abandoned-Cart-Email-25x35.jpg 25w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Herman-Miller-Abandoned-Cart-Email-35x50.jpg 35w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Herman-Miller-Abandoned-Cart-Email-346x490.jpg 346w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Herman-Miller-Abandoned-Cart-Email-220x312.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Herman-Miller-Abandoned-Cart-Email-385x546.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></figure></div>



<p>What’s smart about this email is the way they start with three words, and then use those as steps to encourage prospects to take that final action that will make the product theirs.&nbsp;<br></p>



<h3><strong>iii. The “Are You Broke?” Email</strong></h3>



<p>Okay, you definitely don’t want to ask your prospects if they’re broke, but you can’t blame a girl for trying to add a bit of humor, right?<br></p>



<p>The purpose of this email is to remind customers that their payment failed for some reason and then encourage them to try again or update their payment information.<br></p>



<p>This strategy is primarily for subscription-based products where recurring payments happen automatically, and customers don’t pay manually and can see when payments fail.<br></p>



<p>Following up on failed payments is key if you want to prevent involuntary churn.<br></p>



<p>Here’s how we do at Sleeknote:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="400" height="640" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Sleeknote-Follow-Up-Email.gif" alt="Sleeknote Follow-Up Email" class="wp-image-73979"/></figure></div>



<p>We let people know their payment failed and ask them to update their credit card information.<br></p>



<p>(And in true Sleeknote style, we couldn’t resist adding a funny GIF).<br></p>



<p>This email has a goal completion of 88%, which means 88% of the users who read this email update their credit card and their payment no longer fails.<br></p>



<h2 id="3"><strong>3. Time-Based Follow-Up Emails</strong></h2>



<p>Following up once isn’t always enough.<br></p>



<p>That’s why it’s a good idea to set up scheduled and time-based follow-up emails.<br></p>



<p>Here are three situations where the time-based follow-up email can be used to get prospects reactivated.<br></p>



<h3><strong>i. The “Did You Forget About Me?” Email</strong></h3>



<p>A common experience among marketers is unanswered emails.<br></p>



<p>We send so many emails and only a fraction of them are answered to our annoyance.<br></p>



<p>While we can’t force people to answer our emails, we can encourage them by sending a follow-up email.<br></p>



<p>For instance, if you’ve sent out an email asking for people’s opinion on a new product or a survey, and only a small percentage has responded, you should send a follow-up email and try to get more people to respond.<br></p>



<p>Just because people didn’t respond the first time, doesn’t necessarily mean they didn’t want to, it just means something prevented them from doing it.<br></p>



<p>Send them a friendly reminder that you could really use their help, and remember to exclude the people who’ve already responded.<br></p>



<p>As a rule of thumb, you should always follow up at least three times before giving up.<br></p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="https://thewebsitegroup.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">The Website Group</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="508" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Website-Group-Follow-Up-Email.jpg" alt="The Website Group Follow-Up Email" class="wp-image-73983" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Website-Group-Follow-Up-Email.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Website-Group-Follow-Up-Email-300x254.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Website-Group-Follow-Up-Email-380x322.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Website-Group-Follow-Up-Email-41x35.jpg 41w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Website-Group-Follow-Up-Email-59x50.jpg 59w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Website-Group-Follow-Up-Email-579x490.jpg 579w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Website-Group-Follow-Up-Email-220x186.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Website-Group-Follow-Up-Email-385x326.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>This email was the fourth and last follow-up email I received because I hadn’t responded to the first three emails.<br></p>



<p>I was really impressed with the writing style in all the emails (you know how I love a good laugh), and, of course, I ended up answering this last follow-up email.<br></p>



<p>You can automate all your follow-up emails and schedule them to go out x amount of days after your previous email.<br></p>



<h3><strong>ii. The “I’m Begging You to Come Back” Email</strong></h3>



<p>We hate losing potential customers (who doesn’t?), so just because you sent an abandoned cart email that wasn’t opened or clicked, doesn’t mean you should give up.<br></p>



<p>(Remember the magic number three)<br></p>



<p>Following up on abandoned cart emails is just as important as following up on everything else.<br></p>



<p>Here’s how <a href="https://www.beardbrand.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Beardbrand</a> follows up on abandoned carts&#8230;<br></p>



<p>Email 1 (The personal outreach):<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="243" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-1.jpg" alt="Beardbrand Follow-Up Email 1" class="wp-image-73919" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-1.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-1-300x122.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-1-380x154.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-1-86x35.jpg 86w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-1-123x50.jpg 123w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-1-220x89.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-1-385x156.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>Email 2 (including scarcity):<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-2.jpg" alt="Beardbrand Follow-Up Email 2" class="wp-image-73923" width="450" height="679" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-2.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-2-199x300.jpg 199w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-2-380x573.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-2-23x35.jpg 23w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-2-33x50.jpg 33w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-2-325x490.jpg 325w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-2-220x332.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-2-385x581.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /></figure></div>



<p>Email 3 (Last chance):&nbsp;<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-3.jpg" alt="Beardbrand Follow-Up Email 3" class="wp-image-73927" width="450" height="625" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-3.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-3-216x300.jpg 216w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-3-380x528.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-3-25x35.jpg 25w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-3-36x50.jpg 36w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-3-353x490.jpg 353w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-3-220x305.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Follow-Up-Email-3-385x535.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /></figure></div>



<p>Using scarcity in your follow-up emails can trigger your readers to take action because you’re tapping into their fear of missing out.<br></p>



<p>You can also try offering a discount to give them that final push towards completing their purchase.<br></p>



<h3><strong>iv. The “Yay! You Bought Something” Email</strong></h3>



<p>Lastly, you shouldn’t forget to follow up with new customers.<br></p>



<p>You want to reward people for becoming customers, to keep them coming back to buy more.<br></p>



<p>Send them a simple thank you email after they’ve purchased something, to let them know you appreciate them or send them bonus information about their new purchase.<br></p>



<p>This is especially effective in the travel industry. If a customer has bought a trip, you should send them a guide to the destination and help them make the most of their trip (so they’ll buy from you again next time).<br></p>



<p>Here’s an email I got after purchasing a trip to Costa Rica with <a href="https://www.gadventures.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">G Adventures</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/G-Adventures-Follow-Up-Email-2.jpg" alt="G Adventures Follow-Up Email" class="wp-image-73951" width="450" height="610" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/G-Adventures-Follow-Up-Email-2.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/G-Adventures-Follow-Up-Email-2-221x300.jpg 221w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/G-Adventures-Follow-Up-Email-2-380x515.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/G-Adventures-Follow-Up-Email-2-26x35.jpg 26w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/G-Adventures-Follow-Up-Email-2-37x50.jpg 37w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/G-Adventures-Follow-Up-Email-2-362x490.jpg 362w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/G-Adventures-Follow-Up-Email-2-220x298.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/G-Adventures-Follow-Up-Email-2-385x522.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /></figure></div>



<p>Notice how they also mention that I’ll be receiving more emails like this during my trip, so I know that I should be checking my inbox for tips while I’m there.</p>



<p>You can also follow up with recent customers and encourage them to take further action.<br></p>



<p>Perhaps you have an app you can promote or a loyalty program you would like them to join?<br></p>



<p>People are more likely to accept these inquiries after they’ve made a purchase.<br></p>



<p>You can also do like <a href="https://www.amazon.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Amazon</a>, and ask for feedback on customer’s recent purchase:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="608" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Amazon-Follow-Up-Email.jpg" alt="Amazon Follow-Up-Email" class="wp-image-73911" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Amazon-Follow-Up-Email.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Amazon-Follow-Up-Email-296x300.jpg 296w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Amazon-Follow-Up-Email-380x385.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Amazon-Follow-Up-Email-35x35.jpg 35w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Amazon-Follow-Up-Email-49x50.jpg 49w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Amazon-Follow-Up-Email-484x490.jpg 484w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Amazon-Follow-Up-Email-220x223.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Amazon-Follow-Up-Email-385x390.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p class="has-text-align-center"><em>Source: <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://reallygoodemails.com/" target="_blank">ReallyGoodEmails</a><br></em></p>



<div style="height:40px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<p>The purpose of following up with customers is not only to boost sales and get feedback but also to keep your brand top of mind.<br></p>



<div style="height:40px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


