<h2>Table of Contents</h2>



<p><a href="#1">1. Align Your Body Copy With Your Subject Line</a></p>



<p><a href="#2">2. Use Actionable Language</a></p>



<p><a href="#3">3. Establish Relevancy</a></p>



<p><a href="#4">4. Personalize</a></p>



<p><a href="#5">5. Focus on Benefits Over Features</a></p>



<h2 id="1"><strong>1. Align Your Body Copy With Your Subject Line</strong></h2>



<p>A good email subject line goes beyond the typical clickbait.<br></p>



<p>It gives your reader a preview of what they can expect to find in the email when they open it.<br></p>



<p>Here’s another way to look at it:<br></p>



<p>Look at your subject line as a promise…<br></p>



<p>&#8230;and then fulfill that promise in your email copy.<br></p>



<p>(You don’t want to make a promise you can’t keep).<br></p>



<p>This doesn’t mean you can’t get creative with your subject line and provoke curiosity.<br></p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="https://www.beardbrand.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Beardbrand</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="39" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Subject-Line.jpg" alt="Beardbrand Subject Line" class="wp-image-75984" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Subject-Line.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Subject-Line-300x20.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Subject-Line-380x25.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Subject-Line-180x12.jpg 180w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Subject-Line-250x16.jpg 250w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Subject-Line-220x14.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Subject-Line-385x25.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>They promise their reader the secret to the perfect mustache curl (I don’t have a mustache, but I still opened this email out of curiosity).<br></p>



<p>When reading this subject line, you expect to find the secret in the email, and Beardbrand delivers:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="789" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Email-Copy.jpg" alt="Beardbrand Email Copy" class="wp-image-75980" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Email-Copy.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Email-Copy-228x300.jpg 228w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Email-Copy-380x500.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Email-Copy-27x35.jpg 27w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Email-Copy-38x50.jpg 38w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Email-Copy-373x490.jpg 373w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Email-Copy-220x289.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Beardbrand-Email-Copy-385x506.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>







<p>Delivering on your promise creates trust, and readers know that when they open an email from you (because the subject line encouraged them to), they know the content of the email will deliver on the promise made in the subject line, and they’re more likely to open your emails.<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-group is-style-shadow-box has-sleek-grey-background-color has-background"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<h3><strong>Further Reading</strong></h3>



<div style="height:40px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<ul><li><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/email-subject-lines" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">The 115 Best Email Subject Lines We’ve Ever Seen</a></li></ul>
</div></div>



<h2 id="2"><strong>2. Use Actionable Language</strong></h2>



<p>Your emails all have ONE purpose no matter who you are or who you’re writing to:<br></p>



<p><em>To get people to take action!</em><br></p>



<p>It’s the single most important thing for any business looking to drive engagement and revenue.<br></p>



<p>If you don’t get people to act on your emails, you’re doing something wrong.<br></p>



<h3><strong>How to Get Your Readers to Take Action</strong></h3>



<p>You need to tell people what to do, and you need to do it more than once throughout your email copy.<br></p>



<p>Email copywriting is different from writing a blog post, for instance, because you have to invite people to take TWO actions::<br></p>



<ol><li>They need to open your email, and</li><li>they need to click-through to your target page.</li></ol>



<p>That’s why it’s important that email copywriting isn’t limited to the email copy itself. It includes everything from the subject line, to your <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/write-powerful-cta" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">call-to-action</a> (CTA), and your PS.<br></p>



<p>When it comes to the copy of your email, there are many different ways to write and there’s no <em>one</em> way of doing it.<br></p>



<p>Email copywriting has been (and still is for many) about writing a short email where each sentence has earned its place and supports the CTA of the email.<br></p>



<p>However, something many marketers forget is that there’s a way to sell without making every sentence a sales pitch…<br></p>



<p>&#8230;<a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/story-based-emails" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">storytelling</a>.<br></p>



<p>The concept of storytelling isn’t new, and you’re probably already doing it if you’re writing blog posts or other types of long-form content.<br></p>



<p>You can use storytelling in your emails, too, making the content of your emails the value, and your CTA the “second” value, almost like a PS.<br></p>



<p>The idea here is that if your emails are valuable and relevant to your audience, they’re more likely to click your CTA, even though it isn’t the focus of the email.<br></p>



<p>A great example is <a href="http://bensettle.com/p4/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Ben Settle</a>, who sends an email to his prospects EVERY day with the same CTA to subscribe to his physical newsletter “<a href="http://emailplayers.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Email Players Newsletter</a>”, but with a different story each day.<br></p>



<p>Ben uses the concept of “infotainment” to promote his product, and his purpose is to get people addicted to his emails—more than he wants them to buy his product because he believes the first matters most:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="1024" height="482" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image9-2-1024x482.png" alt="Email" class="wp-image-76016" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image9-2-1024x482.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image9-2-300x141.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image9-2-768x362.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image9-2-380x179.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image9-2-600x283.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image9-2-760x358.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image9-2-74x35.png 74w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image9-2-106x50.png 106w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image9-2-740x348.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image9-2-220x104.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image9-2-385x181.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image9-2.png 1030w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></div>



<p>Here’s a recent example:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="896" height="831" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image8.jpg" alt="Following The Story Email" class="wp-image-76020" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image8.jpg 896w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image8-300x278.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image8-768x712.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image8-380x352.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image8-600x556.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image8-760x705.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image8-38x35.jpg 38w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image8-54x50.jpg 54w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image8-528x490.jpg 528w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image8-220x204.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image8-385x357.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 896px) 100vw, 896px" /></figure></div>







<p>He shares a story that’s seemingly irrelevant to his product but evokes curiosity in his readers.&nbsp;<br></p>



<p>He then ends the email by establishing a connection between the story and the product and creates a relevant call-to-action.<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="878" height="752" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image7-3.jpg" alt="Long Story Short Email" class="wp-image-76024" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image7-3.jpg 878w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image7-3-300x257.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image7-3-768x658.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image7-3-380x325.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image7-3-600x514.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image7-3-760x651.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image7-3-41x35.jpg 41w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image7-3-58x50.jpg 58w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image7-3-572x490.jpg 572w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image7-3-220x188.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image7-3-385x330.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 878px) 100vw, 878px" /></figure></div>



<p>He’s not pushing for a sale, but instead encourage his readers to check it out and see if it’s relevant to them (and if they’re smart marketers, it probably is).<br></p>



<h3><strong>Don’t Yell at Your Prospects</strong></h3>



<p>Now, you might have noticed how I’ve CAPITALIZED certain words and phrases in this post to emphasize a point. But be careful when you do it in your emails.<br></p>



<p>This is another big difference between writing a blog post and email copywriting.<br></p>



<p>You have limited space to work with when writing emails, and you need to get to the point a lot faster than you do with other types of content.<br></p>



<p>It can be tempting to capitalize your CTA or even whole sentences in your email that you don’t want people to overlook. But the problem is that it can easily appear as if you’re yelling at people—and no one likes to be yelled at.<br></p>



<p>Let me illustrate:<br></p>



<p>“SHOP THE LATEST DRESSES TODAY”<br></p>



<p>Vs.<br></p>



<p>“Shop the latest dresses today”<br></p>



<p>How did the first sentence sound in your head compared to the second?<br></p>



<p>A bit louder and aggressive, right?<br></p>



<p>I’m not saying capitalizing certain words won’t work because sometimes it can, but be careful how you use it.<br></p>



<p>Here’s a great example from an email I got from <a href="https://backlinko.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Brian Dean</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="287" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Brian-Dean-Email.jpg" alt="Brian Dean Email" class="wp-image-75988" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Brian-Dean-Email.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Brian-Dean-Email-300x144.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Brian-Dean-Email-380x182.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Brian-Dean-Email-73x35.jpg 73w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Brian-Dean-Email-105x50.jpg 105w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Brian-Dean-Email-220x105.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Brian-Dean-Email-385x184.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>Here the capitalization is used to emphasize the word and its meaning, and because only the one word in the sentence is capitalized, it doesn’t feel like I’m being yelled at.<br></p>



<p>As a rule of thumb, you should refrain from capitalizing entire sentences, and stick to single words that help emphasize your point.<br></p>



<h2 id="3"><strong>3. Establish Relevancy</strong></h2>



<p>With the massive amount of emails sent every day, you should be grateful whenever a subscriber opens your email.<br></p>



<p>With that said, your emails MUST be relevant to the individual receiver if you want them to keep <a href="https://www.lyntonweb.com/inbound-marketing-blog/10-reasons-nobody-reads-your-inbound-marketing-emails" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">opening your emails</a>.<br></p>



<p>In fact, <a href="http://info.raptmedia.com/blog/future-of-content-report-part-1" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">63% of consumers</a> say they’d think more positively of a brand if it gave them content that was more valuable, interesting or relevant.<br></p>



<p>You only have a few seconds to convince your reader that your email is worth their time, which is why you need to establish relevance right away and meet them where they are in the <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/the-buyers-journey" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">buyer&#8217;s journey</a>.<br></p>



<p>To quote Robert Collier: “Always enter the conversation already occurring in the customer&#8217;s mind.”<br></p>



<p>If a potential customer <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/abandoned-cart-emails" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">abandons their cart</a>, you need to send an email and try to convince them to complete their purchase.<br></p>



<p>Eliminate any questions or concerns the reader might have by addressing them in your email copy.<br></p>



<p>Why did they leave their cart?<br></p>



<p>Perhaps the price was too high, or they didn’t have the time to finish. Whatever the reason is, you need to consider it when writing effective emails.<br></p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="https://casper.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Casper</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="400" height="729" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Casper-Email.gif" alt="Casper Email" class="wp-image-75992"/></figure></div>



<p>They establish relevancy right away by letting you know you left an item in your cart, and show you which item it is.<br></p>



<p>Because Casper knows there are several reasons why people abandon their cart, they encourage a dialogue to eliminate the obstacles that prevent people from buying.<br></p>



<p>Sending the right emails to the right prospects at the right time is more important than ever, and the only way to do so is by <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/e-commerce-email-segmentation" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">segmenting your audience</a> into different target groups based on your <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/buyer-personas" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">buyer personas</a>.<br></p>



<h2 id="4"><strong>4. Personalize</strong></h2>



<p>It should no longer come as a surprise that you should personalize your email copy for your receiver.<br></p>



<p>But what many e-commerce brands don’t realize, is that personalization goes beyond a merge tag with the receiver’s name in the greeting.<br></p>



<p>I know it’s impossible to write personal emails to every single prospect on your list, but there are a few hacks you can use to make your email copy <em>appear</em> as if it was written for the individual.<br></p>



<p>Besides the importance of relevance established above, you should always write in the second person.<br></p>



<p>This means your company is more <em>reader-centric</em> rather than business-centric.<br></p>



<p>Here’s an example from <a href="https://www.curioos.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Curioos</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="714" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Curioos-Email.jpg" alt="Curioos Email" class="wp-image-75996" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Curioos-Email.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Curioos-Email-252x300.jpg 252w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Curioos-Email-380x452.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Curioos-Email-29x35.jpg 29w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Curioos-Email-42x50.jpg 42w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Curioos-Email-412x490.jpg 412w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Curioos-Email-220x262.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Curioos-Email-385x458.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>Notice how many times they use the second person in just three sentences…Nine times!<br></p>



<p>Even though this email is automated, it seems more personal because the focus is on the receiver and describes what’s in it for the receiver (more on this later).<br></p>



<p>Also, <a href="https://www.accenture.com/t20161011T222718Z__w__/us-en/_acnmedia/PDF-34/Accenture-Pulse-Check-Dive-Key-Findings-Personalized-Experiences.pdfla=en" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">75% of consumers</a> say they’re more likely to buy from a retailer that recognizes them by name, recommends options based on past purchases, OR knows their purchase history.<br></p>



<p>Here’s another example from Beardbrand:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="663" height="292" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image10.jpg" alt="Yo! Email From Beardbrand" class="wp-image-76028" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image10.jpg 663w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image10-300x132.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image10-380x167.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image10-600x264.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image10-79x35.jpg 79w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image10-114x50.jpg 114w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image10-220x97.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/image10-385x170.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 663px) 100vw, 663px" /></figure></div>



<p>At first glance, there’s not much personalization in this email…But then, notice the PS.<br></p>



<p>The Tree Ranger Utility Balm was the actual item that was left in the cart!<br></p>



<p>This not only makes the email personal, it also reinforces the receiver’s choice of product, and makes them more inclined to go back and buy.<br></p>



<p>There are many ways of writing emails that are personal but doesn’t require hours of work. The more you segment your audience and send trigger based emails, you can automate most of your emails and still keep them personal and relevant.<br></p>



<h2 id="5"><strong>5. Focus on Benefits Over Features</strong></h2>



<p>How often have you received an email with a description of how awesome a product is and a CTA telling you to buy now?<br></p>



<p>Maybe you’ve even sent these out yourself?<br></p>



<p>I have…unfortunately…<br></p>



<p>Too many businesses focus on explaining and showing new features, new product launches, and so on.<br></p>



<p>To quote <a href="https://www.iwillteachyoutoberich.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Ramit Sethi</a>: “That’s great for YOU, but how does this help ME?”<br></p>



<p>That’s the question every prospect asks themselves when receiving an email like that.<br></p>



<p>Instead, you need to scrap all the egocentric BS (pardon my french), and instead focus on the value your potential customers will get from using your product.<br></p>



<p>What’s the problem your product will help them solve?<br></p>



<p>Put yourself in the shoes of your target audience, and think about what they’re struggling with or what they want to achieve.<br></p>



<p>Take this example from <a href="https://www.dollarshaveclub.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)">Dollar Shave Club</a>:<br></p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img width="600" height="860" src="https://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Dollar-Shave-Club-Email.jpg" alt="Dollar Shave Club Email" class="wp-image-76000" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Dollar-Shave-Club-Email.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Dollar-Shave-Club-Email-209x300.jpg 209w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Dollar-Shave-Club-Email-380x545.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Dollar-Shave-Club-Email-24x35.jpg 24w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Dollar-Shave-Club-Email-35x50.jpg 35w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Dollar-Shave-Club-Email-342x490.jpg 342w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Dollar-Shave-Club-Email-220x315.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Dollar-Shave-Club-Email-385x552.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></figure></div>



<p>They address the problem right away: Shaving can be a costly affair, and then they provide a solution: The same (or better) quality for a third of competitors&#8217; prices.<br></p>



<p>It doesn’t have to be more complicated than that.<br></p>



