<h2><strong>Don’t Neglect Your Email Copy</strong></h2>



<p>Writing compelling email copy isn’t rocket science, but it does require researching your audience and figuring out the writing style and triggers they respond best to.<br></p>



<p>If you adopt the notion that every word has to earn its way into your email copy, you’ll automatically think more about how you construct your sentences to support the overall message of your email—which will reflect positively on your bottom line.<br></p>



<p>Start by taking a look at your most recent email campaigns.<br></p>



<p>What would you have done differently knowing what you know now?<br></p>



<p>When you know the answer, you’ll know how to write copy for your next email.<br></p>



